1
00:00:10,733 --> 00:00:17,333
<i>So, Pryvaxil is a maintenance
drug for hallucinations.</i>

2
00:00:20,333 --> 00:00:21,967
<i>We will replace the contents
of the bottle.</i>

3
00:00:22,100 --> 00:00:24,167
<i>When will we enter
the vulture's nest?</i>

4
00:00:24,300 --> 00:00:25,567
<i>I already know who owns the car.</i>

5
00:00:25,700 --> 00:00:27,233
<i> You look familiar.</i>

6
00:00:27,367 --> 00:00:28,567
<i> Is this your car?</i>

7
00:00:28,700 --> 00:00:28,933
<i> Yes.</i>

8
00:00:29,067 --> 00:00:29,533
<i> Why?</i>

9
00:00:29,667 --> 00:00:31,000
<i> Bring my wife out!</i>

10
00:00:31,133 --> 00:00:32,533
<i>Do you want me to blow
your jaw off?</i>

11
00:00:32,667 --> 00:00:34,100
<i>- You again?
- Bring my wife out!</i>

12
00:00:34,267 --> 00:00:34,900
<i> Do you know me?</i>

13
00:00:35,033 --> 00:00:36,167
<i> How can I forget you?</i>

14
00:00:36,300 --> 00:00:38,500
<i>I just danced with you,
and you told me your life story.</i>

15
00:00:38,633 --> 00:00:40,600
<i> I'll be shameless.</i>

16
00:00:40,733 --> 00:00:42,867
<i>Do you know a regular job
I can apply for?</i>

17
00:00:43,000 --> 00:00:45,067
<i> I can be your helper again!</i>

18
00:00:45,200 --> 00:00:47,600
<i>I'm sure I can convince
Aunt Jade.</i>

19
00:00:47,733 --> 00:00:49,733
<i>I want to get back
what she stole from me.</i>

20
00:00:49,867 --> 00:00:51,033
<i> I am Mookie's only mother.</i>

21
00:00:51,167 --> 00:00:55,500
<i>None of those twin demons
can be Mookie's mother.</i>

22
00:01:33,933 --> 00:01:35,500
Hello, Leticia.

23
00:01:37,433 --> 00:01:39,033
Yes.

24
00:01:39,167 --> 00:01:41,200
Emma has gone silent.

25
00:01:42,467 --> 00:01:43,867
And I have been fine

26
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:48,300
and peaceful ever since I
started taking my meds.

27
00:01:48,433 --> 00:01:50,800
And I have you to thank
for that.

28
00:01:50,933 --> 00:01:53,700
<i> Miss Ligaya, too.</i>

29
00:01:53,833 --> 00:01:55,367
<i> She triggered you, right?</i>

30
00:01:55,500 --> 00:01:57,267
<i>That's why you took your
medicine.</i>

31
00:01:57,400 --> 00:01:58,767
<i>Why don't you treat her
for a meal?</i>

32
00:02:06,100 --> 00:02:07,300
Are you crazy?

33
00:02:07,433 --> 00:02:11,700
I'm punishing her
by not feeding her.

34
00:02:11,833 --> 00:02:13,867
And you want me to give her
a treat?

35
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:15,400
I have to go.

36
00:02:15,567 --> 00:02:17,600
I need to take care
of Danilo now.

37
00:02:32,800 --> 00:02:33,867
Jade.

38
00:02:36,200 --> 00:02:37,767
Jade, don't try to surprise me.

39
00:02:39,567 --> 00:02:41,067
Come on.

40
00:02:42,100 --> 00:02:45,300
I just want to steal
a kiss from you.

41
00:02:45,433 --> 00:02:47,900
But since you caught me...

42
00:02:52,333 --> 00:02:53,467
Love,

43
00:02:55,333 --> 00:02:58,433
I know you're looking for Emma
behind my back.

44
00:03:00,467 --> 00:03:04,433
So, did you find her?

45
00:03:08,667 --> 00:03:11,167
Emma isn't a stranger.

46
00:03:13,033 --> 00:03:14,933
She's still my wife. Right?

47
00:03:18,900 --> 00:03:20,567
What do you mean?

48
00:03:21,967 --> 00:03:24,600
So what does that make me?

49
00:03:24,733 --> 00:03:27,833
Did you forget that
I'm your fiancee?

50
00:03:29,067 --> 00:03:31,467
Jade, I understand that.

51
00:03:31,600 --> 00:03:34,733
But don't deprive me
of the right

52
00:03:34,867 --> 00:03:37,567
to find the woman who left me.

53
00:03:37,700 --> 00:03:45,367
I want to confront her and ask
how she could leave her family.

54
00:03:45,500 --> 00:03:48,233
<i> Olive, calm down.</i>

55
00:03:48,367 --> 00:03:51,167
<i>Even if he digs through
the entire country,</i>

56
00:03:51,300 --> 00:03:53,333
<i> he will no longer find Emma.</i>

57
00:03:53,467 --> 00:03:55,433
<i> So don't antagonize him.</i>

58
00:03:55,600 --> 00:03:58,300
<i>Be the fiancee he needs you
to be.</i>

59
00:03:58,433 --> 00:04:01,333
<i> Nice and supportive.</i>

60
00:04:01,467 --> 00:04:02,633
Okay, love.

61
00:04:05,233 --> 00:04:07,667
To be honest,
I'm just concerned about you.

62
00:04:09,067 --> 00:04:13,167
Because I see you suffering.

63
00:04:15,200 --> 00:04:19,233
But if that's what you want
to do, okay.

64
00:04:19,367 --> 00:04:21,067
I will stay out of it.

65
00:04:23,133 --> 00:04:24,300
Even though it hurts.

66
00:04:25,733 --> 00:04:26,967
Wait, Jade.

67
00:04:31,367 --> 00:04:33,733
Thank you for understanding.

68
00:04:35,100 --> 00:04:36,233
Thank you.

69
00:04:41,433 --> 00:04:42,400
<i> See?</i>

70
00:04:42,533 --> 00:04:44,500
<i> That's how you do it, Olive!</i>

71
00:04:44,633 --> 00:04:48,600
<i>He sees you as an ally,
not an enemy.</i>

72
00:04:48,733 --> 00:04:50,300
<i> Play with it.</i>

73
00:04:50,433 --> 00:04:51,567
<i> Ride with it.</i>

74
00:04:51,700 --> 00:04:54,233
<i>He'll eventually get tired
of searching.</i>

75
00:04:55,433 --> 00:04:56,533
Excuse me, love.

76
00:04:57,833 --> 00:04:59,333
Hello, Loida?

77
00:04:59,467 --> 00:05:01,333
Miss Jade, I'm sorry.

78
00:05:01,500 --> 00:05:04,900
I received a high-paying job
offer.

79
00:05:05,033 --> 00:05:06,333
What?

80
00:05:06,467 --> 00:05:08,867
No! You can't do that.

81
00:05:09,000 --> 00:05:11,233
Loida, you can't resign.

82
00:05:11,367 --> 00:05:13,367
Why? How much did they offer
you?

83
00:05:13,500 --> 00:05:16,667
25 thousand pesos per month.

84
00:05:16,800 --> 00:05:18,667
I can offer a higher amount.

85
00:05:18,800 --> 00:05:21,100
I can give you 35 thousand pesos
a month.

86
00:05:21,233 --> 00:05:25,267
Please, Loida. I don't want to
find a new helper.

87
00:05:25,400 --> 00:05:27,500
Thank you for everything,
Miss Jade,

88
00:05:27,633 --> 00:05:30,400
but I'm already okay with their
offer.

89
00:05:30,533 --> 00:05:31,600
Bye.

90
00:05:31,733 --> 00:05:32,400
Loi...

91
00:05:32,533 --> 00:05:34,367
Hello!

92
00:05:34,533 --> 00:05:35,867
Why?

93
00:05:36,000 --> 00:05:37,600
What's the problem with Loida?

94
00:05:37,733 --> 00:05:39,367
She resigned from her job, love!

95
00:05:39,500 --> 00:05:40,500
What?

96
00:05:40,633 --> 00:05:42,300
Why didn't you accept it?

97
00:05:42,433 --> 00:05:44,200
That was a big offer.

98
00:05:44,333 --> 00:05:45,867
Most of the time,

99
00:05:46,000 --> 00:05:48,433
it's already midnight when she
lets me go home.

100
00:05:48,567 --> 00:05:50,700
I have no time for my kids.

101
00:05:50,833 --> 00:05:55,967
On the other hand, you asked me
if I can work at night.

102
00:05:56,100 --> 00:06:00,067
It matters to me that you have
time for them.

103
00:06:00,200 --> 00:06:02,333
You know mothers like us.

104
00:06:02,467 --> 00:06:05,633
Our children matter to us.

105
00:06:05,767 --> 00:06:10,833
So we should make the most
out of our time with them.

106
00:06:11,000 --> 00:06:12,933
Thank you so much, Miss Emma.

107
00:06:13,067 --> 00:06:16,233
Rest assured that everything
you told me

108
00:06:16,367 --> 00:06:17,667
will be just between us.

109
00:06:17,800 --> 00:06:19,433
Thank you, Loida.

110
00:06:19,567 --> 00:06:23,067
You're a big help in getting
Mookie back from Jade.

111
00:06:26,767 --> 00:06:28,900
<i>I want to make it up
to my daughter.</i>

112
00:06:29,033 --> 00:06:32,567
<i>We don't know how long we
can stay with them,</i>

113
00:06:32,700 --> 00:06:36,133
<i>hug and kiss them,
and care for them.</i>

114
00:06:36,267 --> 00:06:39,233
<i>If someone stops us from being
mothers to our children,</i>

115
00:06:39,367 --> 00:06:43,233
<i>we will do everything to take
down what's blocking our way.</i>

116
00:06:43,400 --> 00:06:43,900
Mookie.

117
00:06:44,067 --> 00:06:45,067
Hi, Dad.

118
00:06:45,200 --> 00:06:46,833
Oh, it's Flor.

119
00:06:46,967 --> 00:06:47,867
Dad.

120
00:06:48,000 --> 00:06:49,033
Hi, baby girl.

121
00:06:49,167 --> 00:06:49,900
Hello.

122
00:06:53,433 --> 00:06:54,667
<i> Darn you!</i>

123
00:06:54,800 --> 00:06:55,733
<i> Ma'am!</i>

124
00:06:55,867 --> 00:06:57,400
<i> You're a traitor.</i>

125
00:06:57,533 --> 00:06:58,633
<i> Ma'am!</i>

126
00:07:01,700 --> 00:07:03,533
<i> You never listen!</i>

127
00:07:03,667 --> 00:07:05,100
<i> Get lost!</i>

128
00:07:05,233 --> 00:07:06,400
<i> Get lost!</i>

129
00:07:06,533 --> 00:07:08,267
What are you doing here?

130
00:07:10,133 --> 00:07:15,367
Flor needs a job, Auntie.

131
00:07:15,533 --> 00:07:18,800
That solves your problem.

132
00:07:18,933 --> 00:07:23,467
Your auntie's looking
for a new helper.

133
00:07:23,600 --> 00:07:26,233
Loida resigned.

134
00:07:26,367 --> 00:07:27,633
Really?

135
00:07:27,767 --> 00:07:30,333
Auntie Jade,
please hire Flor.

136
00:07:31,800 --> 00:07:33,133
Well...

137
00:07:33,267 --> 00:07:38,567
I'm not sure if Flor
is someone I can trust.

138
00:07:40,500 --> 00:07:41,867
Auntie Jade.

139
00:07:46,100 --> 00:07:47,133
Baby girl...

140
00:07:49,667 --> 00:07:51,367
Please, Auntie Jade.

141
00:07:53,267 --> 00:07:56,067
I trust Flor.

142
00:07:56,200 --> 00:07:59,200
And we were together
for a long time.

143
00:07:59,333 --> 00:08:02,533
She's hardworking
and responsible.

144
00:08:02,667 --> 00:08:05,233
And she cares for me.

145
00:08:05,367 --> 00:08:06,933
Yes, Ma'am.

146
00:08:07,067 --> 00:08:11,267
And I'll make sure to do
whatever you tell me to do.

147
00:08:11,400 --> 00:08:12,533
Well...

148
00:08:14,267 --> 00:08:16,600
Come on. Hire Flor.

149
00:08:16,733 --> 00:08:19,867
It's better than hiring
a stranger.

150
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:21,533
Yes, Auntie.

151
00:08:21,700 --> 00:08:25,167
And I am so comfortable
with Flor.

152
00:08:27,000 --> 00:08:28,267
Fine.

153
00:08:28,400 --> 00:08:31,667
Since it looks like they like
you.

154
00:08:34,033 --> 00:08:37,500
So, Flor, like Loida,
you'll be a stay-out maid.

155
00:08:38,700 --> 00:08:43,200
And I hope you'll do a great job
taking care of our family.

156
00:08:43,333 --> 00:08:44,333
Thank you, Auntie.

157
00:08:44,467 --> 00:08:47,100
Yes! I will, Ma'am.
I promise you that.

158
00:08:47,233 --> 00:08:48,300
Thank you.

159
00:08:48,433 --> 00:08:48,933
Thank you, Danilo.

160
00:08:49,067 --> 00:08:49,867
Thank you, Mookie.

161
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:50,867
Thank you, Ma'am.

162
00:08:52,767 --> 00:08:53,833
Thank you.

163
00:08:56,367 --> 00:08:57,433
Thank you.

164
00:09:24,000 --> 00:09:25,733
Where is it?

165
00:09:28,467 --> 00:09:29,267
Maybe it's here.

166
00:09:32,967 --> 00:09:33,900
Not here.

167
00:09:51,033 --> 00:09:52,400
Maybe here.

168
00:09:57,200 --> 00:09:58,233
Gotcha.

169
00:10:01,667 --> 00:10:07,300
<i>This causes hot temper,
irritability, anger,</i>

170
00:10:07,433 --> 00:10:11,300
<i>paranoia, and, the best part,
hallucinations.</i>

171
00:10:45,533 --> 00:10:47,700
I need to take my meds.

172
00:11:20,000 --> 00:11:21,067
Seriously?

173
00:11:23,067 --> 00:11:25,633
Flor is going to make me wear
wrinkled clothes?

174
00:11:27,167 --> 00:11:28,067
Flor?

175
00:11:29,733 --> 00:11:30,867
Flor!

176
00:11:32,967 --> 00:11:34,700
Flor, come here!

177
00:11:37,867 --> 00:11:39,167
Flor!

178
00:11:39,300 --> 00:11:41,500
<i> Please take effect.</i>

179
00:11:41,667 --> 00:11:42,567
Flor!

180
00:11:50,200 --> 00:11:51,233
Who's that?

181
00:12:00,633 --> 00:12:02,133
What's happening?

182
00:12:02,267 --> 00:12:03,700
What's happening?

183
00:12:05,267 --> 00:12:06,267
Oh my god!

184
00:12:07,467 --> 00:12:09,300
Come out here! Who are you?

185
00:12:11,067 --> 00:12:13,567
Show yourself to me!
Where are you?

186
00:12:13,700 --> 00:12:14,500
What's happening?

187
00:12:16,900 --> 00:12:18,333
What's happening?

188
00:12:18,467 --> 00:12:25,033
No!

189
00:12:25,167 --> 00:12:26,400
Who are you?

190
00:12:27,700 --> 00:12:29,200
Where is it coming from?

191
00:12:31,700 --> 00:12:33,033
Emma?

192
00:12:33,167 --> 00:12:34,600
Emma?

193
00:12:34,733 --> 00:12:36,367
No!

194
00:12:36,500 --> 00:12:37,900
You're not real!

195
00:12:38,033 --> 00:12:39,800
Stay away from me!

196
00:12:39,933 --> 00:12:41,867
You're not real! No!

197
00:12:42,000 --> 00:12:43,733
No!

198
00:12:43,867 --> 00:12:45,200
No!

199
00:12:45,333 --> 00:12:47,233
Get out of here!

200
00:12:47,367 --> 00:12:49,000
Stay away from me!

201
00:12:49,167 --> 00:12:50,167
You're not real!

202
00:12:50,300 --> 00:12:50,900
Jade!

203
00:12:51,033 --> 00:12:52,133
Jade!

204
00:12:52,267 --> 00:12:52,967
- What's happening here?
- You're just my imagination!

205
00:12:53,100 --> 00:12:53,900
No!

206
00:12:54,033 --> 00:12:54,800
Why?

207
00:12:54,933 --> 00:12:56,267
Jade, what's the matter?

208
00:12:58,267 --> 00:13:00,867
- Take me away from her!
- Jade!

209
00:13:01,000 --> 00:13:03,333
Jade, that's Mookie!
What's wrong with you?

210
00:13:03,467 --> 00:13:04,600
Why?

211
00:13:04,733 --> 00:13:07,200
Flor, what's going on here?
Why is Jade behaving like this?

212
00:13:07,333 --> 00:13:08,733
I don't know.

213
00:13:08,867 --> 00:13:12,033
I came here because I heard her
screaming.

214
00:13:12,167 --> 00:13:14,367
She's so scared of me.
She told me I was Emma.

215
00:13:14,500 --> 00:13:16,233
- Jade, calm down.
- No!

216
00:13:16,367 --> 00:13:16,867
Jade!

217
00:13:17,000 --> 00:13:18,833
No!

218
00:13:21,000 --> 00:13:22,100
- Jade!
- Oh no!

219
00:13:22,267 --> 00:13:24,733
- I'll follow your Aunt Jade.
- I'll go with you. Dad!

220
00:13:24,867 --> 00:13:25,633
Jade!

221
00:13:26,933 --> 00:13:28,733
How pitiful.

222
00:13:40,700 --> 00:13:41,300
Hello, Emma.

223
00:13:42,433 --> 00:13:44,333
ZX took effect instantly.

224
00:13:44,467 --> 00:13:48,400
Jade ran like crazy.

225
00:13:48,533 --> 00:13:50,533
Are you okay, Flor?

226
00:13:50,667 --> 00:13:52,000
You can leave.

227
00:13:52,133 --> 00:13:53,533
Your mission is over.

228
00:13:53,667 --> 00:13:55,000
What do you mean leave?

229
00:13:55,167 --> 00:13:58,433
Why would I leave now that your
plan has already succeeded?

230
00:13:58,567 --> 00:13:59,700
I'll stay here.

231
00:13:59,833 --> 00:14:02,967
I'll keep watch to know
what's going on.

232
00:14:03,100 --> 00:14:05,100
I'll call you later. Bye.

233
00:14:12,267 --> 00:14:15,433
We're about to take down Jade.

234
00:14:17,533 --> 00:14:19,867
Just a little more,

235
00:14:20,000 --> 00:14:22,800
and she'll end up in the mental
hospital.

236
00:14:25,200 --> 00:14:27,133
Just like what she did to me.

237
00:14:27,267 --> 00:14:30,733
She'll also experience the
feeling of being driven crazy.

238
00:14:30,900 --> 00:14:34,433
And it'll be worse because
she's really insane.

239
00:14:37,400 --> 00:14:39,433
I can finally take Mookie back.

240
00:14:39,567 --> 00:14:41,467
We'll be together again.

241
00:14:52,533 --> 00:15:00,667
We can build our own syndicate
once we take down that monster.

242
00:15:01,500 --> 00:15:03,400
We can easily do that.

243
00:15:03,533 --> 00:15:05,333
Is that a new business, boss?

244
00:15:06,800 --> 00:15:07,867
Of course!

245
00:15:08,000 --> 00:15:09,867
We can do that.

246
00:15:13,933 --> 00:15:14,533
Okay.

247
00:15:16,167 --> 00:15:16,933
Next.

248
00:15:18,433 --> 00:15:20,233
This is going to be intense.

249
00:15:23,500 --> 00:15:24,833
Are you guys ready?

250
00:15:41,633 --> 00:15:43,200
What's happening to me?

251
00:15:43,333 --> 00:15:45,600
I'm taking my medicine
religiously.

252
00:15:45,733 --> 00:15:46,833
I should be fine by now.

253
00:15:49,300 --> 00:15:50,133
No.

254
00:15:52,033 --> 00:15:53,467
No.

255
00:15:53,600 --> 00:15:55,900
I can't let this happen to me.

256
00:15:58,200 --> 00:15:59,900
Ligaya!

257
00:16:00,033 --> 00:16:02,200
What's happening to you?
Why are you shivering?

258
00:16:07,533 --> 00:16:08,567
What's happening to you? Ligaya!

259
00:16:08,733 --> 00:16:09,667
Hey!

260
00:16:11,200 --> 00:16:12,300
No.

261
00:16:12,433 --> 00:16:13,333
No.

262
00:16:13,467 --> 00:16:14,567
No.

263
00:16:14,700 --> 00:16:16,467
You can't die.

264
00:16:16,600 --> 00:16:19,500
You can't die on me, Ligaya.
I won't let that happen!

265
00:16:20,900 --> 00:16:23,500
You left me before.

266
00:16:23,633 --> 00:16:26,433
I won't let you do
that to me again.

267
00:16:26,567 --> 00:16:28,167
Ligaya! What's wrong with you?

268
00:16:34,000 --> 00:16:35,733
What's happening to you?

269
00:16:41,567 --> 00:16:42,567
Caloy!

270
00:16:42,700 --> 00:16:43,567
Caloy!

271
00:16:45,567 --> 00:16:47,433
Caloy, come here quick!

272
00:16:54,400 --> 00:16:55,433
Ligaya!

273
00:16:55,567 --> 00:16:56,600
Hey!

274
00:16:56,733 --> 00:16:58,333
Ligaya, what's going on?

275
00:17:01,667 --> 00:17:02,633
Hurry up!

276
00:17:02,767 --> 00:17:03,667
I'm on it.

277
00:17:05,200 --> 00:17:06,700
Are we going to San Bartolome,
Ma'am?

278
00:17:06,833 --> 00:17:09,133
That's the nearest hospital
from here.

279
00:17:09,267 --> 00:17:10,633
Of course not.

280
00:17:10,767 --> 00:17:12,133
Are you even thinking?

281
00:17:12,267 --> 00:17:15,433
What if Ligaya wakes up
and reports us?

282
00:17:15,600 --> 00:17:17,733
Bring her to Artemis Pharmacy's
stockroom.

283
00:17:17,867 --> 00:17:19,167
I will send a doctor there.

284
00:17:21,200 --> 00:17:22,900
Ligaya!

285
00:17:23,033 --> 00:17:25,167
You can't die yet.

286
00:17:25,300 --> 00:17:27,533
Don't you dare let go.

287
00:17:27,667 --> 00:17:32,000
Because I will punish you even
in the afterlife.

288
00:17:35,600 --> 00:17:36,933
Really, Ma'am?

289
00:17:37,067 --> 00:17:38,167
How will you do that?

290
00:17:38,300 --> 00:17:39,533
You will have to die, too.

291
00:17:40,367 --> 00:17:41,567
Am I talking to you?

292
00:17:41,700 --> 00:17:42,867
Go!

293
00:17:43,000 --> 00:17:45,167
- Okay.
- Go on! Take her. Hurry up!

294
00:17:53,367 --> 00:17:54,400
Jade?

295
00:17:54,533 --> 00:17:55,333
Love!

296
00:17:56,867 --> 00:17:57,933
Hi, Mookie.

297
00:17:59,633 --> 00:18:01,767
Where have you been?
I've been looking for you.

298
00:18:01,900 --> 00:18:03,833
We've been looking for you, too.

299
00:18:03,967 --> 00:18:04,667
Where did you go?

300
00:18:04,800 --> 00:18:05,200
Where have you been?

301
00:18:07,567 --> 00:18:09,200
Someone asked for directions,

302
00:18:09,333 --> 00:18:13,133
so I told him where Opal Street
was.

303
00:18:13,267 --> 00:18:14,700
I went to the clubhouse.

304
00:18:14,833 --> 00:18:17,033
I just wanted to take a walk.

305
00:18:17,167 --> 00:18:18,767
I'm just getting a little bit
stressed.

306
00:18:18,900 --> 00:18:20,133
I wanted to get some fresh air.

307
00:18:22,233 --> 00:18:24,233
Auntie Jade, are you okay?

308
00:18:24,867 --> 00:18:27,433
You know what?
You look really bothered.

309
00:18:27,567 --> 00:18:30,600
Is there something
you want to tell us?

310
00:18:30,733 --> 00:18:32,467
About what happened earlier...

311
00:18:32,600 --> 00:18:33,800
what was that?

312
00:18:36,333 --> 00:18:38,833
This is nothing, baby girl.

313
00:18:38,967 --> 00:18:40,867
I'm just stressed at work.

314
00:18:41,000 --> 00:18:45,133
There's an alleged stealing
of formula in Activora.

315
00:18:45,267 --> 00:18:47,667
The Artemis Pharmacy
got involved.

316
00:18:47,800 --> 00:18:49,833
This could bring down
the company.

317
00:18:49,967 --> 00:18:51,933
I'm really so stressed.

318
00:18:52,067 --> 00:18:54,533
A lot has been happening
lately, so...

319
00:18:55,833 --> 00:18:58,767
To be honest, I broke down quite
a few times.

320
00:18:58,900 --> 00:19:02,467
Ma'am, why did you call me Emma?

321
00:19:02,600 --> 00:19:05,100
Does she have something
to do with Artemis?

322
00:19:05,233 --> 00:19:06,633
Of course not.

323
00:19:06,767 --> 00:19:08,800
I didn't call you Emma.

324
00:19:08,933 --> 00:19:10,167
I'm not a liar, Ma'am.

325
00:19:10,467 --> 00:19:12,000
So you're telling me
I'm the liar?

326
00:19:12,633 --> 00:19:15,500
Don't you dare accuse me
of something I did not do.

327
00:19:16,033 --> 00:19:18,233
I'm getting stressed!
I'm being pressured!

328
00:19:18,367 --> 00:19:19,233
Jade.

329
00:19:19,367 --> 00:19:21,000
So, please don't add up
to my problems!

330
00:19:21,133 --> 00:19:22,800
Jade.

331
00:19:22,933 --> 00:19:23,667
It's her fault!

332
00:19:23,800 --> 00:19:24,367
Jade! That's enough!

333
00:19:24,500 --> 00:19:26,067
Are you saying I'm a liar?

334
00:19:26,200 --> 00:19:27,233
Jade.

335
00:19:27,367 --> 00:19:30,367
Why didn't you tell us that
you're breaking down?

336
00:19:31,833 --> 00:19:34,167
We could've consulted a doctor.

337
00:19:34,300 --> 00:19:35,500
You know what?

338
00:19:35,633 --> 00:19:38,300
All I need you to do is to shut
up!

339
00:19:39,200 --> 00:19:41,467
Let me solve my problem
in the company!

340
00:19:42,167 --> 00:19:43,033
Excuse me!

341
00:19:43,167 --> 00:19:44,033
Jade!

342
00:19:47,100 --> 00:19:50,000
Mookie, Danilo, I swear,
she called me Emma.

343
00:19:50,133 --> 00:19:51,800
And she was so scared.

344
00:19:54,767 --> 00:19:56,667
She seems to become
like Ma'am Olive.

345
00:19:56,800 --> 00:19:59,267
She's getting paranoid.

346
00:19:59,400 --> 00:20:00,567
What do you call that?

347
00:20:00,700 --> 00:20:01,433
She seems to be losing her mind.

348
00:20:01,600 --> 00:20:02,567
Right, Mookie?

349
00:20:02,700 --> 00:20:03,633
So scary.

350
00:20:03,767 --> 00:20:06,833
Maybe Auntie Jade is just
getting stressed.

351
00:20:06,967 --> 00:20:08,400
She's not like that.

352
00:20:09,367 --> 00:20:10,133
No.

353
00:20:10,267 --> 00:20:14,067
It seems she's becoming like
Olive.

354
00:20:14,200 --> 00:20:16,033
She seems to be going crazy.

355
00:20:17,567 --> 00:20:19,933
So scary. I wonder what's
happening to Ma'am Jade.

356
00:20:24,500 --> 00:20:25,600
What?

357
00:20:25,733 --> 00:20:27,900
You brought Ligaya
to the hospital?

358
00:20:28,033 --> 00:20:29,867
Looks like she's dying, Ma'am.

359
00:20:31,900 --> 00:20:33,100
You idiot!

360
00:20:34,000 --> 00:20:36,867
I don't pay you to disobey me!

361
00:20:37,667 --> 00:20:40,300
Didn't I tell you to go
to Artemis' stockroom?

362
00:20:40,967 --> 00:20:42,800
Sorry, Ma'am. I panicked.

363
00:20:47,100 --> 00:20:48,233
Shut up!

364
00:20:48,367 --> 00:20:49,233
Shut up!

365
00:20:49,367 --> 00:20:50,233
Shut up!

366
00:20:52,400 --> 00:20:54,167
No. Not you.

367
00:20:54,300 --> 00:20:55,467
Which hospital?

368
00:20:57,233 --> 00:20:59,067
Okay, okay. I'll go there.

369
00:21:07,333 --> 00:21:08,867
Hello, Leticia?

370
00:21:09,033 --> 00:21:10,067
Come with me.

371
00:21:10,200 --> 00:21:12,133
Let's meet at San Bartolome
Community Hospital.

372
00:21:12,267 --> 00:21:13,367
Now.

373
00:21:24,633 --> 00:21:25,733
Hello, Emma?

374
00:21:33,033 --> 00:21:33,400
Ma'am Jade.

375
00:21:33,533 --> 00:21:34,900
You, imbecile.

376
00:21:35,933 --> 00:21:36,967
Hi, Doc.

377
00:21:37,100 --> 00:21:39,133
How's Ligaya?

378
00:21:39,267 --> 00:21:40,967
I'm so worried about her

379
00:21:41,100 --> 00:21:44,467
because she's been my nanny
since I was a baby.

380
00:21:44,633 --> 00:21:48,933
She was already senile when she
got out of the house.

381
00:21:50,167 --> 00:21:52,500
And it's Caloy's fault!

382
00:21:52,633 --> 00:21:53,467
What did you do?

383
00:21:55,700 --> 00:21:59,300
Doc, why did Miss Ligaya
have a seizure?

384
00:21:59,433 --> 00:22:02,233
She suffered from severe
dehydration

385
00:22:02,367 --> 00:22:03,900
and prolonged starvation.

386
00:22:04,033 --> 00:22:05,500
Ah, okay.

387
00:22:05,633 --> 00:22:07,433
My gosh.

388
00:22:07,567 --> 00:22:10,333
It's been a while since I last
fed her.

389
00:22:11,933 --> 00:22:13,633
Doc, how is she?

390
00:22:13,767 --> 00:22:15,300
Is Ligaya doing okay now?

391
00:22:15,467 --> 00:22:17,133
Can we bring her home now?

392
00:22:17,267 --> 00:22:20,100
We took care of her condition,
but she's still unconscious.

393
00:22:20,233 --> 00:22:21,467
She's stable, though.

394
00:22:21,600 --> 00:22:24,133
We brought her to the
ward for monitoring.

395
00:22:24,267 --> 00:22:26,467
- Monitoring?
- Monitoring.

396
00:22:36,200 --> 00:22:38,767
Why did Caloy have to bring
Ligaya here?

397
00:22:40,133 --> 00:22:41,267
This place looks okay.

398
00:22:42,367 --> 00:22:43,800
Okay?

399
00:22:43,933 --> 00:22:45,867
Look around you.

400
00:22:46,000 --> 00:22:49,100
There are lots of indigenous
people here.

401
00:22:49,933 --> 00:22:54,667
What if Ligaya bumps into
someone she knows?

402
00:22:54,800 --> 00:22:57,300
What if Kurtsy or Wiro is here?

403
00:22:57,433 --> 00:22:59,433
Or what if there's someone
here she has played cards

404
00:22:59,567 --> 00:23:01,333
or mahjong with? Or a relative?
Cousin? Husband!

405
00:23:01,467 --> 00:23:02,900
I don't know!

406
00:23:03,033 --> 00:23:04,800
You mean your dad?

407
00:23:04,933 --> 00:23:06,467
Wait.

408
00:23:06,600 --> 00:23:08,433
Do you know anything
about your dad?

409
00:23:08,567 --> 00:23:10,133
Is your dad still alive?

410
00:23:10,267 --> 00:23:11,733
I don't know anything.

411
00:23:11,867 --> 00:23:15,067
And I don't care about that
father you're talking about!

412
00:23:16,133 --> 00:23:17,200
I'm just being careful.

413
00:23:17,933 --> 00:23:20,433
No one must recognize Ligaya.

414
00:23:21,133 --> 00:23:23,567
I need to get her out of here
now.

415
00:23:27,400 --> 00:23:30,367
And why not in a private room?
Why a ward?

416
00:23:30,900 --> 00:23:32,767
What if she catches a disease?

417
00:23:32,900 --> 00:23:34,333
She might die!

418
00:23:34,467 --> 00:23:35,700
Well, you heard the doctor.

419
00:23:35,833 --> 00:23:37,833
He said your mother is doing
okay.

420
00:23:37,967 --> 00:23:42,200
Will you stop calling
that old woman my mother?

421
00:23:42,333 --> 00:23:43,467
Well, she is.

422
00:23:43,600 --> 00:23:45,233
And you're concerned about her.

423
00:23:46,800 --> 00:23:49,067
I'm not concerned about her.

424
00:23:49,200 --> 00:23:51,367
I don't want her to die

425
00:23:51,500 --> 00:23:54,200
because I still have many plans
for her.

426
00:23:59,600 --> 00:24:00,400
Hey!

427
00:24:03,067 --> 00:24:04,000
That's Emma!

428
00:24:05,133 --> 00:24:06,133
That's Emma!

429
00:24:06,267 --> 00:24:07,733
Emma's here!

430
00:24:07,867 --> 00:24:09,133
She's following me!

431
00:24:09,267 --> 00:24:10,133
Can you relax?

432
00:24:10,267 --> 00:24:11,467
What are you doing here?

433
00:24:11,600 --> 00:24:12,867
What do you need from me?

434
00:24:13,000 --> 00:24:13,667
Keep quiet.

435
00:24:13,800 --> 00:24:15,967
Emma's here!

436
00:24:16,100 --> 00:24:17,800
She's looking at me!

437
00:24:39,500 --> 00:24:40,267
<i> Olive?</i>

438
00:24:41,533 --> 00:24:43,133
<i> Why did you bring me here?</i>

439
00:24:53,667 --> 00:24:59,567
<i>Mister, I'm begging you.
Please save me from Olive.</i>

440
00:25:03,233 --> 00:25:04,233
<i> Ador?</i>

441
00:25:05,933 --> 00:25:07,967
<i> You can't escape me, Ligaya.</i>

442
00:25:08,100 --> 00:25:10,100
<i> Don't!</i>

443
00:25:10,233 --> 00:25:14,233
<i> Don't!</i>

444
00:25:25,067 --> 00:25:26,733
Olive isn't here.

445
00:25:32,733 --> 00:25:34,567
- Thank goodness.
- I'm glad you're awake now.

446
00:25:38,000 --> 00:25:38,933
Who are you?

447
00:25:39,267 --> 00:25:40,433
Are you a doctor?

448
00:25:40,567 --> 00:25:41,433
No, I'm not.

449
00:25:41,567 --> 00:25:42,500
I'm Caloy.

450
00:25:42,633 --> 00:25:43,967
I'm Miss Jade's messenger.

451
00:25:44,100 --> 00:25:45,300
You are Jade's henchman?

452
00:25:46,767 --> 00:25:49,467
- I can't be here.
- Don't remove that.

453
00:25:49,600 --> 00:25:50,867
You'll get hurt.

454
00:25:51,000 --> 00:25:55,633
- It's bleeding...
- Don't touch me!

455
00:25:55,767 --> 00:25:56,500
Help me!

456
00:25:56,633 --> 00:25:58,733
My daughter locked me up.

457
00:25:58,867 --> 00:26:00,467
- This is her henchman.
- That's not true.

458
00:26:00,600 --> 00:26:01,800
What do you mean not true?

459
00:26:01,933 --> 00:26:03,033
Look at my wounds!

460
00:26:03,167 --> 00:26:04,033
Look at that.

461
00:26:04,167 --> 00:26:05,167
They chain me.

462
00:26:05,300 --> 00:26:06,833
I brought you here
to the hospital.

463
00:26:06,967 --> 00:26:07,433
Wait!

464
00:26:07,567 --> 00:26:08,167
Stay away from her!

465
00:26:08,300 --> 00:26:09,300
She's lying!

466
00:26:09,467 --> 00:26:10,633
Stay away from her!

467
00:26:10,767 --> 00:26:11,333
Hey!

468
00:26:11,467 --> 00:26:12,667
Wait!

469
00:26:12,800 --> 00:26:13,800
Stay there!

470
00:26:13,933 --> 00:26:15,433
I brought her here!

471
00:26:15,567 --> 00:26:18,367
She's lying!

472
00:26:18,500 --> 00:26:19,967
Stay out of it!

473
00:26:20,100 --> 00:26:21,833
She's lying!

474
00:26:26,900 --> 00:26:28,433
Stacy, not now.

475
00:26:28,733 --> 00:26:30,300
I'm bored.

476
00:26:30,433 --> 00:26:32,500
I really want to play, Mookie.

477
00:26:32,633 --> 00:26:33,533
What's wrong with you?

478
00:26:35,500 --> 00:26:38,100
Zayn, that girl is your
girlfriend?

479
00:26:40,333 --> 00:26:41,900
Why are you looking at me?

480
00:26:42,067 --> 00:26:44,567
Emma told you to follow me,
right?

481
00:26:44,700 --> 00:26:46,933
She told me I was here, right?

482
00:26:47,533 --> 00:26:48,500
Go on, Jade.

483
00:26:49,167 --> 00:26:50,300
Panic.

484
00:26:50,900 --> 00:26:51,733
Go crazy.

485
00:26:51,867 --> 00:26:53,900
That's not enough for what you
did to me.

486
00:26:54,467 --> 00:26:56,933
For making me crazy and for
stealing my husband and child.

487
00:26:57,067 --> 00:26:58,667
Did you see a woman?

488
00:26:58,800 --> 00:27:01,267
She's wearing white clothes,
has chinky eyes,

489
00:27:01,400 --> 00:27:02,733
and has white hair.

490
00:27:02,867 --> 00:27:03,833
I didn't.

491
00:27:03,967 --> 00:27:06,700
Bro, I think I saw the woman
you're looking for.

492
00:27:07,133 --> 00:27:08,667
Please help me.

493
00:27:08,800 --> 00:27:10,567
I need your help.
